iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - A 47-year-old Italian man was on Thursday found dead in his room at the Sankara Hotel in Westlands, Nairobi, Kenya.The man had booked into a room on the 4th floor of the posh hotel, where he had been staying since Tuesday.According to Nairobi News, he died after calling for a taxi to pick him up from the hotel.The hotel staff had gone to check&nbsp;on him&nbsp;after he failed to answer calls by the taxi driver. That was when they found his lifeless body near the door of his room.According to Daily Nation, he had injuries&nbsp;to his&nbsp;head.An investigation into his death was launched by the police.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.